      • equalsIgnoreCase

        public static boolean equalsIgnoreCase​(CharSequence l,
                                       CharSequence r)
        Compares two char sequences on assumption and right value is always lower case. Methods converts every char of right sequence before comparing to left sequence.
        Parameters:
        l - left sequence
        r - right sequence
        Returns:
        true if sequences match exactly (ignoring char case)

      • splitLpsz

        public static ObjList<Path> splitLpsz​(CharSequence args)
        Split character sequence into a list of lpsz strings. This function uses space as a delimiter and it honours spaces in double quotes. Main use for this code is to produce list of C-compatible argument values from command line.
        Parameters:
        args - command line
        Returns:
        list of 0-terminated strings
